title: The Bachelorette: Angie Kent throws serious shade at Jessika Power
text:
Angie Kent has thrown serious shade at former Married At First Sight bride Jessika Power, as their bitter feud shows no sign of slowing down.

The ex-Gogglebox star, who debuts as The Bachelorette on Wednesday night, channeled Mariah Carey by saying: 'I don't know her!'

The rivalry between the two women began on Sunday, after Angie was quoted in a newspaper as saying that MAFS was 'super trash'.

Appearing on The Kyle and Jackie O Show, Angie said: 'I don't know Jess. I didn't even watch her season of MAFS because I was in the jungle [on I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here!]

'I don't know her. I don't know where that [the feud] has come from.'

When asked specifically about calling MAFS 'trash', the 29-year-old clarified that she probably meant to say 'car crash television'.

'I don't know her!' The Bachelorette's Angie Kent (pictured) threw serious shade at Married At First Sight star Jessika Power on The Kyle and Jackie O Show on Wednesday

'I love trash,' she added. 'Maybe that's what's upset her?'

Angie was being interviewed on KIIS FM to promote the new season of The Bachelorette, which premieres on Wednesday.

She described herself as a 'lover, not a fighter' and said she didn't want a celebrity feud to distract from her journey.

Harsh words! The rivalry between the two women began on Sunday, after Angie was quoted in a newspaper as saying that MAFS was 'super trash'

'I don't want any dramas. If I've offended her, I don't know what it was,' she said.

After Angie's initial comments about MAFS caught the attention of Jessika on Sunday, the controversial reality star hit back on Instagram.

She blasted Angie as a 'hypocrite' and told her to 'get off [her] high horse'.

Fighting talk! Jessika later called Angie a 'hypocrite' and told her to 'get off [her] high horse'

'On MAFS we all know I had an affair and was seeing Mick and Dan,' she began.

'But Angie, you're dating like 21 guys at once, so which one is more trash? Get off your high horse, this is hypocrisy at its finest.'

The Bachelorette begins Wednesday at 7:30pm on Channel 10
